React:
    is an open source JavaScript Library for building rich User Interface.
    has a Component Based Architecture
    helps write Reusable Code
    is Declarative 
        Means "tell React what you want and React will build the actual UI"
        Oposite is Imperative paradigm where you control the flow of layout and explicitly tell the steps
    handles efficiently updating and rendering the Components
    can be seamlessly integrated into any application

Prerequisites
    HTML
    CSS
    JavaScript - 'this' keyword, filter, map and reduce
    ES6 Features - let & const, arrow functions, template literals, default parameter, object literals, rest and spread operators
        and destructuring assignments

Insall nodejs and any IDE

Course: Fundamentals
        HTTP
        Routing
        Redux
        Utilities
        
To Install Node.js on MacOS    
    brew install node

Check version of Node.js installed 
     node -v

npx : is a npm package runner gets installed with nodejs.

To create new application
    npx create-react-app <application_name>

Note
    npx is a package runner tool that comes with npm 5.2+.

To install required packages and start application
    npm install
    npm start

To create a production build of this application   
    npm run build

    



